.jpg?itok=WmVkxpe0" width="100" height="100" alt="Butter" title="Butter" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/butter">Butter</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">butt-err</span><p>Butter is made when lactic-acid producing bacteria are added to cream and churned to make anâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 small onion, finely chopped">1 small <a href="/glossary/onion" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--6 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">onion</a>, finely chopped<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--6"><article id="node-253826" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/onion"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/onionchop.jpg?itok=Z9o7wXeU" width="100" height="100" alt="Onion" title="Onions are endlessly versatile and an essential ingredient in countless recipes" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/onion">Onion</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">un-yun</span><p>Onions are endlessly versatile and an essential ingredient in countless recipes. Native to Asiaâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="50g fresh white breadcrumbs(from about 4 slices)">50g fresh white breadcrumbs (from about 4 slices)</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="a small handful thyme leaves, plus extra for scattering">a small handful <a href="/glossary/thyme" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">thyme</a> leaves, plus extra for scattering<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-255456" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/thyme"></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/thyme">Thyme</a></h2><p>This popular herb grows in Europe, especially the Mediterranean, and is a member of the mintâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="25g parmesan, coarsely grated">25g <a href="/glossary/parmesan" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--7 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">parmesan</a>, coarsely grated<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--7"><article id="node-259696" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/parmesan"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/parmesan.jpg?itok=Z34jTwkR" width="100" height="100" alt="Parmesan" title="Parmesan is a straw-coloured hard cheese with a natural yellow rind and rich, fruity flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/parmesan">Parmesan</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">parm-ee-zan</span><p>Parmesan is a straw-coloured hard cheese with a natural yellow rind and rich, fruity flavour. Itâ€¦</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>In a large pan of boiling salted water, cook the parsnips and swede, covered, for about 20 minutes until tender. Drain well, then mash them together using a masher or food processor until reasonably smooth but still with a bit of texture. Stir in the soured cream, horseradish and thyme and season with salt and pepper.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Spoon into a buttered shallow ovenproof dish and put to one side.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Make the topping. Melt the butter in a frying pan and cook the onion for 5-6 minutes, until gorgeously golden. Mix in the breadcrumbs and stir to brown and crisp a little. Season with salt and pepper and add the thyme. Take the pan off the heat. Spoon the mixture casually over the top of the mash. Scatter over the parmesan. (Can be made ahead to this point and kept covered in the fridge for up to a day. Or can be frozen for up to a month.)</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Bake with the turkey (190C/gas 5/ fan 170C) for 35-40 minutes if doing from cold, 25-30 minutes if not, or 11â„2-13â„4 hours from frozen (put foil on top, and remove it for the last 10 minutes) â€“ until golden and crisp on top. Serve scattered with a few more thyme sprigs and leaves.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food Vegetarian Christmas, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1164931200" class="text-style-alt">December 2006</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" clas